{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17585641","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17585641"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T08:15:23+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T08:15:23+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14994"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14994","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14994"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.1,0.1,0.17,0.41,0.21]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7682"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66721"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7682","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7682"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14994"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52174"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4908"},{"type":"tags","id":"4936"},{"type":"tags","id":"4940"},{"type":"tags","id":"4945"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"5440"},{"type":"tags","id":"8114"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"18773"},{"type":"contributions","id":"18775"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66721","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/66721"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA two-year-old boy presents with recurrent bacterial and fungal infections since infancy. Genetic testing reveals mutations in genes encoding components of the nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide phosphate (NADPH) oxidase complex. Treatment includes prophylactic antibiotics, antifungal medications, and interferon gamma.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Leucocyte adhesion deficiency type 1","Hyper immunoglobulin M syndrome","X-linked agammaglobulinaemia","Chronic granulomatous disease","Immunoglobulin A deficiency"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient has \u003Cstrong\u003Echronic granulomatous disease\u003C/strong\u003E, characterised by defects in the NADPH oxidase complex that prevents proper neutrophil function. The NADPH oxidase system is crucial for generating reactive oxygen species needed to kill certain pathogens, particularly catalase-positive organisms like \u003Cem\u003EStaphylococcus aureus\u003C/em\u003E and \u003Cem\u003EAspergillus\u003C/em\u003E species.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELeucocyte adhesion deficiency type 1\u003C/strong\u003E involves defects in neutrophil adhesion molecules (CD18), preventing neutrophils from leaving the bloodstream\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHyper immunoglobulin M syndrome\u003C/strong\u003E results from CD40 ligand deficiency, affecting immunoglobulin class switching\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EX-linked agammaglobulinaemia\u003C/strong\u003E involves mutations in Bruton tyrosine kinase leading to absent B cells and all immunoglobulin classes\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EImmunoglobulin A deficiency\u003C/strong\u003E is characterised by selective absence of IgA with normal levels of other immunoglobulins\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETreatment focuses on preventing infections through prophylactic antimicrobials and enhancing immune function with interferon gamma.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Chronic granulomatous disease is caused by defects in NADPH oxidase complex genes, leading to impaired neutrophil killing of catalase-positive organisms.","Treatment of chronic granulomatous disease includes prophylactic antimicrobials and interferon gamma to boost immune function.","The NADPH oxidase complex is essential for generating reactive oxygen species in neutrophils for pathogen killing."],"references":["Holland SM. Chronic granulomatous disease. Hematol Oncol Clin North Am. 2013 Feb;27(1):89-99, viii. doi: 10.1016/j.hoc.2012.11.002. Epub 2012 Nov 22. PMID: 23351990; PMCID: PMC3558921.","Bona, C. A., \u0026 Bonilla, F. A. (2019). Textbook of immunology. CRC press","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52174"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14994"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52174","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/52174"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-01T20:28:11+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-01T20:29:11+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7682"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66721"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emo